  "title": "ADMIN MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Overview</strong></p><p>The Admin Manager is responsible for overseeing and managing the company’s administrative, office management, and support functions to ensure smooth daily operations. This role acts as a key support to management and works closely with HR, Finance, and Operations teams to maintain efficiency, compliance, and a well-organised workplace.</p><p><strong>Roles & Responsibility</strong></p><p><strong>Administrative & Office Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Oversee day-to-day administrative operations to ensure smooth and efficient office functioning.</p></li><li><p>Manage office facilities, equipment, supplies, and vendors (e.g. building management, maintenance, pantry, stationery).</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper documentation, filing systems, and record-keeping practices are maintained.</p></li><li><p>Handle general correspondence, contracts, and administrative coordination.</p></li></ul><p><strong>HR & People Support (Administrative Scope)</strong></p><ul><li><p>Support HR administration including onboarding and offboarding processes.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate work passes, employment documentation, and liaison with MOM or relevant authorities.</p></li><li><p>Maintain employee records, leave tracking, and HR databases.</p></li><li><p>Support company events, staff activities, and internal communications.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Finance & Procurement Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Assist with administrative finance matters such as invoice processing, payment tracking, and expense claims.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with finance teams or external accountants on administrative documentation.</p></li><li><p>Manage procurement processes for office-related purchases and services.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Policy, Compliance & Governance</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with company policies, internal controls, and regulatory requirements.</p></li><li><p>Support audits by preparing and maintaining administrative records and documentation.</p></li><li><p>Assist in reviewing and updating administrative policies and procedures.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Management & Coordination</strong></p><ul><li><p>Act as a key point of contact between management, staff, and external parties.</p></li><li><p>Provide administrative support to senior management as required.</p></li><li><p>Identify opportunities to improve administrative processes and operational efficiency.</p></li><li><p>Supervise and guide administrative staff, if applicable.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Management, or related fields.</p></li><li><p>At least 3-5 years of relevant administrative or office management experience, preferably in a manufacturing or engineering environment.</p></li></ul>",
